Jeanette Chabalala, News24(File) Multimedia &nbsp; &nbsp; User Galleries &nbsp; &nbsp; News in Pictures Send us your pictures &nbsp; &nbsp; Send us your stories Pretoria - More than 100 people were injured in a train accident in Rossyln train station in Pretoria. Spokesperson for Best Care Ambulance Services Xander Loubser who is on scene said the incident happened when two coaches collided. &nbsp; &ldquo;About 90% of the patients are slightly injured and 10% are in a serious condition,&rdquo; Loubser said. &nbsp; No fatalities reported. &nbsp; Pretoria police were on their way to the scene. &nbsp; More to follow.&nbsp; 24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.